U.K. Maker of Zero-Emission Vehicles in Administration, FT Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-07T05:13:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/u-k-maker-of-zero-emission-vehicles-in-administration-ft-says.html
Modec Ltd., a closely held U.K.
maker of electric delivery vans, has gone into administration
with debts of more than 40 million pounds ($65 million), the
Financial Times reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
